full_text:
I'm not quitting music. I'm taking a hiatus until I can create music that I'm happy with again.

I'll try to end on a positive. It's likely that I will be studying music formally at a university starting next year. Hopefully that will give me the inspiration to start over again.
full_text(utf-8): b"I'm not quitting music. I'm taking a hiatus until I can create music that I'm happy with again.\n\nI'll try to end on a positive. It's likely that I will be studying music formally at a university starting next year. Hopefully that will give me the inspiration to start over again."

full_text: Have I fallen out of love with music? Certainly not. Probably closer to the opposite. My understanding of music is greater than it ever was, but that only serves as a burden that prevents me from creating new music. I don't want to do anything halfway anymore.
full_text(utf-8): b"Have I fallen out of love with music? Certainly not. Probably closer to the opposite. My understanding of music is greater than it ever was, but that only serves as a burden that prevents me from creating new music. I don't want to do anything halfway anymore."

full_text: I feel a sense of guilt that in the year where I've had more time to work on music than ever before, I've spent the least amount of time doing so. It became a source of stress rather than enjoyment, and my desire for a new sound ultimately prevented me from completing anything.
full_text(utf-8): b"I feel a sense of guilt that in the year where I've had more time to work on music than ever before, I've spent the least amount of time doing so. It became a source of stress rather than enjoyment, and my desire for a new sound ultimately prevented me from completing anything."

full_text: TheDiabolicalWaffle is a moniker I've wanted to shed for a long time now. It was something I thought of in my early teens and have been ridiculed for many times over the years. I grew tired of it but felt like I couldn't change without an excuse or improvements in the music.
full_text(utf-8): b"TheDiabolicalWaffle is a moniker I've wanted to shed for a long time now. It was something I thought of in my early teens and have been ridiculed for many times over the years. I grew tired of it but felt like I couldn't change without an excuse or improvements in the music."

full_text: I was diagnosed with depression this year, lost family members, fell out of touch with every social contact both online and irl, developed a chronic condition and struggled with various physical injuries and mishaps. I felt like both my body and mind were failing me.
full_text(utf-8): b'I was diagnosed with depression this year, lost family members, fell out of touch with every social contact both online and irl, developed a chronic condition and struggled with various physical injuries and mishaps. I felt like both my body and mind were failing me.'

full_text: I've had the date December 1 locked in for a long time. I was supposed to have new music ready for a rebrand, but my struggles with mental health and various other issues prevented me from seeing anything I was proud of through to completion.
full_text(utf-8): b"I've had the date December 1 locked in for a long time. I was supposed to have new music ready for a rebrand, but my struggles with mental health and various other issues prevented me from seeing anything I was proud of through to completion."

full_text:
It will release as part of a 10 track SoundCloud/Spotify exclusive that aims to fill out and finalise my discography for this alias. 

7 Years was finished over a year ago and was never intended to be released, but I felt it would be wrong to end TheDiabolicalWaffle without it.
full_text(utf-8): b'It will release as part of a 10 track SoundCloud/Spotify exclusive that aims to fill out and finalise my discography for this alias. \n\n7 Years was finished over a year ago and was never intended to be released, but I felt it would be wrong to end TheDiabolicalWaffle without it.'

full_text:

On December 1st, I will release "7 Years", the last ever TheDiabolicalWaffle song.
